Your Birthdate: February 18
Your birthday on the 18th day of the month suggests than you are one who can work well with a group, but still remain someone who needs to maintain individual identity. There is a humanistic or philanthropic approach to business circumstances in which you find yourself. You may have good executive abilities, as you are very much the organizer and administrator. You are broad-minded, tolerant and generous; a compassionate person that can inspire others with imaginative ideas. Some of your feelings may be expressed, but even more of them are apt to be repressed. There is a lot of drama in your personality and in the way you express yourself to others. Oddly enough, you don't expect as much in return as you give.

For all that are upset by the war, please read the article linked below.  Its by LTC Tim Ryan.  He is Commander, Task Force 2-12 Cavalry, First Cavalry Division in Iraq. He led troops into battle in Fallujah late last year and is now involved in security operations for the upcoming elections. He wrote the following during "down time" after the Fallujah operation.

http://www.worldtribune.com/worldtribune/05/breaking2453389.0680555557.html

I really like that article, cause it sums up what I have been trying to say to many of my friends.  I know of marines and army friends who have come home and told me dont believe anything you have read.  I am glad to read this and hope this sheds some light on some other people.

So I am watching the Michael Jackson Documentary on VH1 for the , I think 3rd or 4th time.  There is something about it that has me glued to it.  Its like watching a freak show.  I mean he says the reason he never liked his face was because of acne.  I think there should be a Michael Jackson channel.  Ait the documentary 24 hours a day. 

Last night I went out drinking.  So needless to say I am really tired.  My friends and I rented a luxury limo bus that seats 30 people.  I think, although as fun as it was, those things are a mistake.  Since no one drives home, I think we tend to drink more.  A LOT MORE.  So now this morning I pay for it.

I WANT TO GO HOME!  The clock is actually laughing at me while its turning the minute hand the wrong way.  I am sick of being here.  Man do I whine.  

So last night Ang and I watch the American Idol Christmas Special.  I admit it.  Laugh all you want guys.  I am secure enough.  Anyway.  Clay is gayer than any queer eye guy.....not that there is anything wrong with that.  I was sickened by something else.  The non comedic banter between Clay and Ruben.  Why. Really Why.  Just sing O Holy night and be done with it.  Oh and on a side note.  Coming from one big guy to a much more bigger guy.  The Sweating, I feel for you Ruben.  Bro I feel your pain.

Good Morning everyone.  I am still trying to setup this page correctly.  Please let me know if you don't see a retro background on this page.  

Let me start off by saying that I need a vacation from my life.  Lately things have been such a mess in my life I can't be a part of it anymore.  I am hoping this journal will help me get out what I need to get out.  I am still deciding whether or not to write down the whole ordeal just to see it in words and maybe get a new perspective on things.  But I don't have time today.  

What I will write is to everyone.

Have a Happy Thanksgiving!
